Philippines Stocks: PAL Holdings, Union Bank, Universal Robina

-- B y   I a n   C .   S a y s o n   a n d   W e i y i   L i m
-- 
2011-07-25T04:20:44Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-25/globe-pal-union-bank-vista-land-philippines-stocks-preview.html
Shares of the following companies
had unusual moves in Philippine trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses, and prices are as of noon close in  Manila .  The Philippine Stock Exchange Index rose 2.14 points, or
0.1 percent, to 4,480.50.  PAL Holdings Inc. (PAL)   surged 21 percent to 6.40 pesos,
the steepest increase since Jan. 14. Philippine Airlines Inc.,
the nation’s largest carrier and unit of the company, posted a
so-called total comprehensive income of $72.5 million in the
year ended March 31, compared with a loss of $14.4 million a
year earlier, as passenger traffic and cargo increased, the
airline said in an e-mailed statement.  Union Bank of the  Philippines  (UBP PM) increased 2 percent
to 62.5 pesos, the biggest advance since March 28. The bank’s
net income climbed to 2.15 billion pesos ($50.7 million) in the
second quarter, from 1.365 billion pesos a year earlier, based
on an e-mailed copy of a financial statement filed to the
Philippine Stock Exchange dated July 22.  Universal Robina Corp. (URC)  , the nation’s second-
largest food and drinks company, dropped 2.5 percent to 47
pesos, after it was cut to “hold” from “buy” by Lovell
Sarreal, an analyst at ATR KimEng Securities Inc. The analyst
has a 12-month share-price estimate of 50.30 pesos.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ian C. Sayson in Manila at 
